 to reductions. These reductions ap- plied only to average rates of subsidy, so particular policies or products could be subject to much higher levels of support. Countries were also allowed to exclude support for a particular product under a de minimis exemption if the value of the support does not exceed 5% of the value of the total production of the commodity; or 5% of the value of total agricultural pro- duction for non-product specific support. (10% for developing countries). 3. Tariffication \u2013 Non-tariff barriers (e.g. quotas) were to be converted into an equivalent tariff. Developing countries were given the option of introducing bound tariff ceilings. 4. Tariffs \u2013 were to be reduced by an aver- age of 36% over 6 years, and with a mini- mum of 15% for each item (24% and 10% for developing countries, 0% for LDCs) 5.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "f87dadd9-22b7-479d-8ac7-47db2de040c0": {"__data__": {"id_": "f87dadd9-22b7-479d-8ac7-47db2de040c0", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/rebuilding-international-food-policy-architecture", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Rebuilding International Food Policy Architecture", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/rebuilding-international-food-policy-architecture", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "9d0ad35a23f96dfa2eb650b3a5e411224664ec665b5ba93fbc9fef8b2bb6fd10"}, "2": {"node_id": "1f4f47a8-6ff8-44cf-b349-1b4848b6b220", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "h