", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/rising-food-and-fuel-prices-asia-and-pacific-causes-impacts-and-policy-responses", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "88112e1afc6c84dc72f550592d3cec7d26bd07ee083bdad000fc03cb92f71702"}}, "hash": "c1c740f0283e59fd0340cf422487fecbc8e3faee3f886658e83bd839d2b63310", "text": "A simple scenario analysis using five variables that captures the above reasons was under taken to evaluate the impact of high food prices on consumer budgets across different expenditure quintiles. Initially, a baseline scenario is assumed with a given level of household income, expenditure, food shares in total expenditure and share of cereal in total food expenditure. These four variables allows for the estimation of the ratio of total consumption to income, total food expenditure, ratio of food expenditure to total income 58 and total expenditure on cereal and non-cereal food expenditure across different expenditure quintiles. Afterwards, an alternative scenario is undertaken with an actual rise in international cereal prices (116%) and pass-through coefficients during 2006-08. The details are given in the annex tables. The", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "b5d60968-ca0f-46dd-9618-96e040d1320a": {"__data__": {"id_": "b5d60968-ca0f-46dd-9618-96e040d1320a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/rising-food-and-fuel-prices-asia-and-pacific-causes-impacts-and-policy-responses", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Rising Fo